[SN]TITLE[SN]
30 youths throw stones at fire crew in Cwmbran

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A fire crew was attacked by about 30 youths throwing stones at them while they were attending to a deliberately-lit rubbish fire in Torfaen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
South Wales Fire and Rescue service said one firefighter was hit on the helmet by a stone but no-one was hurt.
They were called to Beddick in Greenmeadow, Cwmbran, just before 19:00 BST on Saturday.
A spokesperson said: "We will be working closely with the police to identify who was responsible."
